<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Statute lims:pit-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392932" lims:id="392932" bill-origin="commons" bill-type="govt-public" xml:lang="en" in-force="yes" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392933" lims:id="392933"><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392934" lims:id="392934">An Act to provide for the continuation of payments under certain guaranteed income averaging certificates issued by the Pioneer Trust Company</LongTitle><ShortTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392935" lims:id="392935" status="official">Pioneer Trust Payment Continuation Act</ShortTitle><RunningHead lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392936" lims:id="392936">Pioneer Trust Payment Continuation</RunningHead><BillHistory lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392937" lims:id="392937"><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392938" lims:id="392938" stage="assented-to"><Date><YYYY>1985</YYYY><MM>5</MM><DD>16</DD></Date></Stages><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" stage="consolidation"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></Stages></BillHistory><Chapter lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392940" lims:id="392940"><ConsolidatedNumber official="no">P-14.2</ConsolidatedNumber><AnnualStatuteId revised-statute="no"><AnnualStatuteNumber>15</AnnualStatuteNumber><YYYY>1985</YYYY></AnnualStatuteId></Chapter></Identification><Introduction lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392941" lims:id="392941"><Enacts lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392942" lims:id="392942"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392943" lims:id="392943" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate and House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</Text></Provision></Enacts></Introduction><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392944" lims:id="392944"><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392945" lims:id="392945" level="1"><TitleText>Short Title</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392946" lims:id="392946"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392947" lims:id="392947">Short title</MarginalNote><Label>1</Label><Text>This Act may be cited as the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="P-14.2">Pioneer Trust Payment Continuation Act</XRefExternal>.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392948" lims:id="392948" level="1"><TitleText>Agreements</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392949" lims:id="392949"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392950" lims:id="392950">Agreements and arrangements generally</MarginalNote><Label>2</Label><Subsection lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392951" lims:id="392951"><Label>(1)</Label><Text>The Minister of State (Finance), or any officer of the Office of the Superintendent of Financial Institutions designated by the Minister, may, on behalf of Her Majesty, enter into such agreements or arrangements as may be necessary for or incidental to the continuation of payments under and in accordance with the guaranteed income averaging certificates issued by the Pioneer Trust Company for a term of more than five years and outstanding on February 15, 1985.</Text></Subsection><Subsection lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392952" lims:id="392952"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392953" lims:id="392953">Powers</MarginalNote><Label>(2)</Label><Text>Where the Minister or a designated officer enters into an agreement or arrangement under subsection (1), the Minister or officer may do such things and perform such acts as may be necessary for or incidental to carrying out the agreement or arrangement.</Text></Subsection><HistoricalNote><HistoricalNoteSubItem lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392955" lims:id="392955">1987, c. 23, s. 42</HistoricalNoteSubItem></HistoricalNote></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392956" lims:id="392956"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392957" lims:id="392957">Agreement with Saskatchewan</MarginalNote><Label>3</Label><Text>The Minister of State (Finance) may, on behalf of Her Majesty, enter into an agreement with the government of Saskatchewan to provide for the sharing of any costs incurred under this Act.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392958" lims:id="392958" level="1"><TitleText>Appropriation</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392959" lims:id="392959"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392960" lims:id="392960">Appropriation</MarginalNote><Label>4</Label><Subsection lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392961" lims:id="392961"><Label>(1)</Label><Text>The Minister of State (Finance) may, from time to time, pay out of the Consolidated Revenue Fund such amounts as are required for the purposes of section 2.</Text></Subsection><Subsection lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392962" lims:id="392962"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392963" lims:id="392963">Limitation</MarginalNote><Label>(2)</Label><Text>The aggregate of the amounts paid out of the Consolidated Revenue Fund under subsection (1) shall not exceed the aggregate of</Text><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392964" lims:id="392964"><Label>(a)</Label><Text>five million dollars, and</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2003-01-01" lims:fid="392965" lims:id="392965"><Label>(b)</Label><Text>the amounts paid into the Fund that are received pursuant to agreements entered into under section 2.</Text></Paragraph></Subsection></Section></Body></Statute>